text:
Trump knew Alex Acosta gave his buddy Jeffrey Epstein a sweetheart deal that let him keep abusing women & children. 

And then, out of all the Republicans on the planet, Trump made Acosta his Labor Secretary. 

Why?

#releasethefiles https://t.co/Gw7Jl4PKxw

Clinics like HealthWorks provide vital services, for those with or without health insurance, but as the number of uninsured rises, will they’ll be forced to make difficult decisions and cut back on services, making it harder for people to access care. https://t.co/PxtxplLhi9

In #VA11, almost 90,000 people rely on Medicaid & more than 36,000 people are enrolled in marketplace health insurance coverage through the ACA. If we don’t cancel the planned cuts & extend premium tax credits, the ranks of uninsured will skyrocket, driving up costs for everyone. https://t.co/i4Kir4D8yk

This morning I visited @HealthWorksNova, a local nonprofit health center to learn about the work they do and the challenges they face. Unfortunately, the looming health care crisis will make it harder for centers like this to keep our community healthy. https://t.co/MCj4QSTCvV

The priority must be cancelling the health care cuts and passing a bipartisan budget. 

Instead, Trump threw a tantrum & cancelled a planned meeting with Democratic leaders. 

If there’s a shutdown, it’s on him & Republicans. https://t.co/tWf6qTe9a9

Trump walked away from talks to keep the gov’t open & prevent the health care crisis. He calls 322,000 Virginians losing coverage & $1,200 hikes in premiums “unserious.” 

We’re barreling toward a Trump shutdown. He must come to the table & work for a bipartisan budget agreement.
Shanah Tova! Wishing a happy New Year to everyone in our community celebrating Rosh Hashanah. https://t.co/Grbj1eeedL

I haven’t wasted any time in fighting for federal workers. 

I’ve introduced legislation to prevent Trump from downsizing federal agencies and taken up Gerry Connolly’s work for fair pay, merit based hiring, and IVF access. https://t.co/j3bnoAMumb

Proud to fight GOP attacks on health care alongside @BobbyScott, @RepDonBeyer, @RepMcClellan & @RepSuhas. 

At today’s press conference with @ProtectOurCare, we urged Republicans to put politics aside & work with us to protect Medicaid & stop ACA premiums from skyrocketing. https://t.co/6CiSsB3kDf

This weekend, we held our 1st Congress on Your Corner at the Oakton Library. My staff & I spent the afternoon meeting folks, hearing your concerns, & going to work solving problems. Thanks to everyone who stopped by to share your thoughts or say hello. 

We’re here to serve you! https://t.co/IPTekeDijB

On day one, I introduced my first bill to protect federal workers and the vital services they provide to the American people. 

Read my op-ed in @TheHillOpinion to learn more: https://t.co/ofb6vhPthm https://t.co/8zQnetTARA
Trump rages online while a GOP shutdown looms. Families will pay the price with soaring health care costs. Stop the revenge tour. Protect health care now.

It was an honor to help celebrate First Baptist Church of Merrifield’s 155th Anniversary this morning. 

FBCM is a cornerstone of faith, service, and community. I look forward to celebrating many more anniversaries with them. https://t.co/8DOMvBA5fF

Alex Acosta gave Trump’s friend Jeffrey Epstein a sweetheart deal that let him keep abusing women and girls. 

We will leave no stone unturned—and we won’t stop fighting until every survivor gets justice. 

Release the files. https://t.co/cW4UNsAfHH

President Trump and Speaker Johnson: it’s time to deliver what the American people and Fairfax families need—affordable health care and a fully funded, functional government. 

No more chaos, no more excuses. https://t.co/uMPCNzlOU6

Finally, I made my way over to Taste of Annandale to help welcome attendees to this year’s festival. It was incredible to see so many families, pets, and community members celebrating the food and culture of Annandale. https://t.co/H7DJ6PBpXA

Busy day in #VA11! I started my day at Oak Hill Day where folks got a chance to tour the historic Oak Hill in Braddock District and learn about the property’s history and enjoy music and other local activities. https://t.co/v9Sed1YhU5

Trump’s FCC is trying to cancel The View after celebrating Jimmy Kimmel’s takedown. This is a corrupt, unconstitutional assault on free speech. 

I’m demanding FCC Chair Brendan Carr resign & Congress subpoena him so he can explain his violations of his oath to the Constitution. https://t.co/pqtmUQPSZr

I’m still struck by what Alex Acosta displayed yesterday: a callous disregard for the survivors of Epstein’s heinous crimes. 

He shielded Trump’s buddy with a sweet heart deal that allowed the abuse to continue.

We’re not stopping until the truth comes out.  Release the files. https://t.co/xpbrj9bgBI

Today we interviewed Alex Acosta, Trump’s former Labor Secretary and former U.S. Attorney. 

Despite overwhelming evidence, Acosta gave Trump’s pal Jeffrey Epstein a sweetheart plea deal that allowed Epstein to continue raping and abusing. We’re trying to figure out why. https://t.co/oRQyQGgqxI

House Republicans created a health care crisis—slashing Medicaid and raising health care costs. At Trump’s orders, they refuse to work with us. We’re here, ready to negotiate to lower costs. After jamming through their partisan bill, they left. If there’s a shutdown, they own it. https://t.co/IccDaF8NWM

In a time when so much divides America, postal workers keep us united. With 72% of Americans trusting USPS, I’m proud to join the launch of the Congressional Postal Service Caucus to stand up for these essential workers and the service they provide. https://t.co/ZsSnaSWwdW

Excited to join my first @DadsCaucus meeting!

This is an important moment for dads to unite and prevent millions of families from losing their health care coverage when premiums skyrocket.

In my first Oversight hearing, I called out the truth: as families face rising costs, Medicaid cuts, and a looming shutdown—while Trump hides the Epstein files—House Republicans are busy disenfranchising 700,000 D.C. residents to aid Trump’s power grab. https://t.co/QXsikFdDj4

Big news: I’ve been appointed to the Oversight & Government Reform Committee. This is a huge win since it has a major role in issues impacting our community! On the Committee, I’ll fight for federal workers, push back on Trump’s DOGE cuts, & carry forward Gerry Connolly’s legacy. https://t.co/jqxHGFdkqz
Excited to join the fight for transparency and accountability!

Trump ordered House Republicans not to work with us—pushing us toward a shutdown unless they can lock in high prices on health care, groceries & everyday goods. 

I’ll keep fighting to protect Medicaid and lower costs for Fairfax families. https://t.co/dUotIMbdPr

Fairfax families deserve affordable health care. Because of Trump’s harmful policies, 322,000 Virginians risk losing coverage & ACA premiums will spike by $1,200 here in VA-11. 

While Republicans push a shutdown, I’ll keep fighting to protect care & lower costs. https://t.co/qrwvg4f4kI
Proud to join the @HouseDemocrats family as we work to make health care affordable and accessible for every family!

We’ve hit the ground running on day one. Both our DC & Fairfax offices are ready to serve you. 

Visit https://t.co/KK4QDDoaWG to get in touch! https://t.co/hDPWl2jUs7

Trump’s DOGE cuts to USAID & the State Dept — & his failure to implement democracy programs — has emboldened authoritarians. On #DemocracyDay, we’re reminded that leadership means fighting corruption & defending fundamental rights — not adoring dictators as Trump too often does.

Proud to join former HHS Secretary @XavierBecerra, HRSA Administrator Carole Johnson, and VA Delegates to hold the line for Fairfax families against Trump’s devastating Medicaid cuts. 

As Republicans push a shutdown, I’ll fight for affordable care. https://t.co/c0DzuKC8pC

Starting my first full week in Congress with one priority: standing up for Fairfax. I’ll keep sounding the alarm on Trump’s harmful policies and look forward to soon learning my committee assignments. https://t.co/9MWJjhIQkc

My first few days in Congress have been jam-packed! 

✅ Introduced my 1st bill to protect federal workers from unjust DOGE cuts.
✅ Signed the Epstein discharge petition.
✅ Gave my 1st floor speech calling out Trump’s harmful policies.

It’s an honor to serve Fairfax families. https://t.co/bElIFaueSm

Thank you to the @fairfaxparks for having me speak at this year’s Elly Doyle Park Service Awards! Tonight’s awardees are part of the 10,000+ volunteers who help maintain and operate our park system each year. Their dedication and passion for our parks is truly invaluable. https://t.co/ZW4gcc5zrY

It was a perfect day to celebrate the 50th Anniversary of the Hickory Farms Community Association! 

Now more than ever building this sense of community is critical as we weather challenging times. https://t.co/PAphtmrWEf

(2/2): A President with the desire and ability to bring us together would aid in the effort to heal our nation. But that’s not the President we have. So it’s up to all of us — Democrats and Republicans — to find a path forward that ends the bloodshed.

(1/2): The murder of Charlie Kirk should spark a national dialogue and unity around ending political violence and addressing gun violence. Calls for retribution, civil war, or the suppression of political debate are wrong and un-American. https://t.co/GITdja3ti9
Proud to join my Virginia colleagues in condemning political violence. ⬇️

Great to join the @politicshour on @wamu885 to talk about my first few days in Congress, news of the day, & how I plan to serve Fairfax!

Tune in now! https://t.co/7pjr10x6UM https://t.co/IETEkonPkY
I’m honored to join the @NewDemCoalition under the leadership of Chair @RepSchneider, alongside colleagues committed to delivering common-sense solutions for the American people!

(2/2) In Fairfax, we are on the leading edge of the Trump economy, where everyone knows someone who has lost their job due to failed policies. It’s time for Congress to change course and address the rising costs and sputtering economy harming hardworking Americans.

(1/2) Humbled to be sworn in to serve the people of Virginia’s 11th District. On day one, I took to the House floor to highlight how Trump’s DOGE cuts and reckless policies are hurting Fairfax families. https://t.co/G69GvoOVqq
